summary: So, I’ve been thinking a lot about Andi Mack these past days, and yes, the cancellation sucks. It really does, it’s such an...
body:
So, I’ve been thinking a lot about Andi Mack these past days, and yes, the cancellation sucks. It really does, it’s such an amazing show and had so potential to be so much more than it already was. 

But I’m tired. So I’m going to put aside the anger and grief for a moment, because let’s focus on the positive for a moment, yeah? 

We’re watching history in the making. To be apart of that, even as just a viewer, is incredible. Despite restrictions and being held back, this show managed to do so much for representation in modern day media, especially kids media, and I don’t know what’s going to happen next, but I do know that Andi Mack has opened the door for a whole load of new content and I cannot wait for it. 

So I’m 20 years old which is approximately…. way too old to get this emotional over a Disney Channel show, but honestly? Had this been around when I was younger, I’m not kidding, my life would’ve been easier. Maybe I’m exaggerating, but this, this is what kids needs to see. We’ve been watching different variations of the same characters for AGES and finally we have something for people that doesn’t fit that mold. This is the change I’ve been waiting for. (obviously, there’s representation in other disney channel shows as well, but Andi Mack has managed to take it one step further, and is constantly including people we haven’t seen before)

The kid that’s watching that show, the one with a learning disability, the one with anxiety, the one that’s gay, the one with a parent in the army, the one with a different family set up, and so on, that kid is seeing themselves for the first time. Is seen for the first time. And that is more important than I could ever put into words. 

I pretend to be a writer but, man, I’m bad with words.  The point of it all is that, I, among so many more people, am so thankful for Andi Mack, for everything it is and will be. 

So thank you, Andi Mack. For the characters, for the story, the change we need in the world. Thank you.

body:
Tyrus AU “Disaster Gay N°25183” - Introduction

I decided to have another go at making a Tyrus Social Media AU.

In this one, TJ and Amber Kippen are the children of one of the most wealthiest people in the city. They don’t like being known by everybody because of it, but they’re even happier that they have finally found friends who like them for who they are and not for their parents’ money. As fate wanted they both fell in love with one of their best friends. Amber gets to be with the girl of her dreams, while TJ has a really hard time listening to his best friend and at the same time crush, talk about his own crushes, which seem to change every week. To be able to deal with all his problems he has his own secret Twitter account, where he originally calls himself JT, with loads of followers, where he anonymously talks about his life and especially his crush on Cyrus.

This is just a bit of an introduction to their twitter accounts, I don’t know when I’ll specifically start but I’m really excited to do this AU ☺️

Tyrus Crush AU - Part 13: The End

first // previous

personal message at the end

I can’t believe this AU is already finished. It’s been so much fun but I couldn’t think of any way to continue this and be content with it that’s why it’s ending here.

A new AU is already in the making but I’ll take more time for it and be more careful so I can at least go 20 parts without seeing an end (doesn’t mean they won’t get together until the last part this time).

Anyway, thanks everyone who’s messaged me, commented, liked and reblogged my AU, I really hope I helped making the hiatus a bit more bearable and I love you all! 💕
